{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01EhWEGWPnikawAgiDTCNAmw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Analyzing the two peptides against the native NPS sequence (SFRNGVGTGMKKTSFQRAKS):\n\n**PEP-EBF5A06DFA:** `SFRNGVGTGMKK(D-Thr)SFQRAKS`\n- Single modification: T13 → D-Thr (mid-sequence D-amino acid)\n- No N-terminal protection, no C-terminal amidation\n- A mid-sequence D-residue typically disrupts the helical region without compensating gains\n\n**PEP-93846D9997:** `(D-Ser)F(4-F-Phe)NGVGTGMKK(N-Me-Thr)SFQRAKS-NH2`\n- D-Ser1 (aminopeptidase protection)\n- R3 → 4-F-Phe (hydrophobic/aromatic at position 3 — a well-known SAR-driven potency enhancement at NPSR; consistent with the [t-Bu-Ala3]NPS / [Cha3]NPS analog series)\n- N-Me-Thr13 (backbone N-methylation, protease stability)\n- C-terminal amidation (–NH2)\n\nPEP-93846D9997 combines multiple potency- and stability-enhancing modifications, including the canonical position-3 hydrophobic substitution that drives large EC50 reductions in NPS SAR series. PEP-EBF5A06DFA has only a single mid-sequence D-substitution likely to destabilize the active conformation.\n\nPrediction: **PEP-93846D9997** is the more potent peptide."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":527,"cache_read_input_tokens":26229,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":527},"output_tokens":55,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d8b20858-11b1-4c77-8ff6-313fcd3a5862","uuid":"de1f5f5c-c8f1-4b4c-92c5-edda6496d6ba"}
